1) Install from official github dir.
2) Extract and ensure java and javafx is available.
3) set up path

--- configure ruleset ---

4) pmd ruleset for apex https://docs.pmd-code.org/pmd-doc-7.16.0/pmd_rules_apex.html
   $ pmd check -d /some/dir -f text -R apex_ruleset.xml  # -f means output can be html as well

5) pmd, cmd, eslint etc. can be called using sf codeanalyzer plugin 
## or Using SF CodeAnalyser uses 
sf code-analyzer rules --rule-selector pmd --view detail
sf code-analyzer rules --rule-selector pmd --rule-selector therule
sf code-analyzer run --rule-selector eslint:3 --rule-selector retire-js:Recommended

######## Working with ruleset
complete reference -  https://docs.pmd-code.org/pmd-doc-7.16.0/pmd_rules_apex.html
example downloaded from - https://github.com/ChuckJonas/vscode-apex-pmd/blob/master/rulesets/apex_ruleset.xml


